
                                            The police’s David Miller says it is unclear at this stage who the victims are or if anyone else was hurt.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - At least two people have been shot dead at a taxi rank at a mall in Centurion. The police’s David Miller says it is unclear at this stage who the victims are or if anyone else was hurt. He says the killings could be linked to ongoing fights over routes between taxi associations. “I have received reports that two people have been killed. That it's alleged they belong to a part of the taxi associations and our forensic teams are currently on the scene.”